<br>
The best way to use it is to wait until the MTs mob is about 50% dead, then banish one mob.  This will send the executioner back and give you 25 seconds to finish the MTs mob, and still give you time to nuke if banishment is resisted.  <br>
<br>
I had enough mana to banish 3 to 4 rocks per trial, and still use one shock of fiery blades per mob.. sometimes 2 if i got a partial resist the first time.  Followed by mala/malosini, maelstrom of electicity, and 2 to 3 flame bolts of tallon on the boss.  Still ended the fights with 20m or more.<br>
<br>
The only reason i can think not to use banishment, is if you don't want to waste the gems.  70pp per cast does add up. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <br><font color=#333333>- </font><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower>The Magician's Tower</a><font color=#333333> - </font><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32>Class Balance</a> <font color=#333333> - </font><a href="http://www.magecompendium.com/">The Mage Compendium</a><font color=#333333> - </font>  <br><br><table border=0 align=center><tr><td align=center><a href="http://login.ezboard.com/BBSSystem.showUserPaymentScreen" target="_blank">Upgrade your account to ezSupporter...</a></td><td><img src="http://www.ezboard.com/image/spacer.gif" width=15 height=1 border=0></td><td align=center><a href="http://login.ezboard.com/BBSSystem.showUserPaymentScreen" target="_blank">...and never see another ad or pop-up again</a></td></tr></table><CENTER><!-- START BOTTOM AD SCRIPT -->
